{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} {{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |name = Munakata Shrine (胸肩神社) | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = {{image requested|cat=Hirosaki City}} |location = [[Aomori Prefecture]] [[Hirosaki City]] Shinagawa-cho 89 |ISO = JP-02 |latitude_deg = 40 |latitude_min = 35 |latitude_sec = 40.5 |longitude_deg = 140 |longitude_min = 28 |longitude_sec = 41.0 |deity = {{ublist| {{ill|Ichikishimahime|ja|市杵島姫命|1=Ichikishimahime|12=draft|12=draft}} | {{ill|Tagitsuhime|ja|湍津姫命|12=draft|12=draft}} | {{ill|Tachirahime|ja|田心姫命|1=Tagorihime|12=draft|12=draft}} }} |sacred_objects = |rank = |founded = {{ill|Daido|ja|大同|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (807 CE) |chief_priest = |main_hall = |alternative_names = |pilgrimage_sites = |major_festivals = {{ublist| Evening Festival June 30 | Grand Festival July 1 }} |rituals = |map = Japan Aomori }}
'''Munakata Shrine''' (胸肩神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Hirosaki City]], [[Aomori Prefecture]], Japan.
== Enshrined Deities ==
; Three Goddesses : {{ill|Ichikishimahime|ja|市杵島姫命|1=Ichikishimahime|12=draft|12=draft}} : {{ill|Tagitsuhime|ja|湍津姫命|12=draft|12=draft}} : {{ill|Takiribime|ja|田心姫命|1=Tagorihime|12=draft|12=draft}} ; Protector of Roads : Guardian of transportation, safe childbirth, fertility, learning, commerce, and industries. ; deity associated with water : Found near springs, rivers, ponds, and the sea. ; Guardian deity for those born in the year of the Dragon or Snake : Before [[Munakata Taisha]] in [[Fukuoka Prefecture]] became the main shrine, the site enshrined Benzaiten. During the [[Meiji era]], the shrine began worshiping Munakata deities, similarly linked to water. Locally, these deities are still referred to as "Benten-sama."
== History ==
* In {{ill|Daido|ja|大同|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (807 CE), General {{ill|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|ja|坂上田村麻呂|12=draft|12=draft}} founded the shrine, enshrining Benzaiten at a site called Ōno. * In {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (1662 CE), the shrine was relocated to its current location.
== Festivals ==
The Grand Festival is held annually on July 1, with an Evening Festival the day before on June 30.
The Evening Festival includes various ceremonial and entertainment events.
== Access ==
; Railway : 15-minute walk from {{ill|Hirosaki Station|ja|弘前駅|12=draft|12=draft}} on the JR Line.
== External Links == * [https://www.muanakta.com/ Official Website]
