'''Munakata Shrine''' (胸肩神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Hirosaki City]], [[Aomori Prefecture]], Japan.
== Enshrined Deities ==
; Three Goddesses : {{ill|Ichikishima-hime|ja|市杵島姫命|1=Ichikishima-hime}} : {{ill|Tagitsuhime|ja|湍津姫命|1=Tagitsuhime|2=ja|3=タギツヒメ|4=zh|5=多岐都比賣命|6=fr|7=Tagitsuhime}} : {{ill|Takiribime|ja|田心姫命|1=Tagorihime}} ; Protector of Roads : Guardian of transportation, safe childbirth, fertility, learning, commerce, and industries. ; deity associated with water : Found near springs, rivers, ponds, and the sea. ; Guardian deity for those born in the year of the Dragon or Snake : Before [[Munakata Taisha]] in [[Fukuoka Prefecture]] became the main shrine, the site enshrined Benzaiten. During the [[Meiji era]], the shrine began worshiping Munakata deities, similarly linked to water. Locally, these deities are still referred to as "Benten-sama."
== History ==
* In {{ill|Daido|ja|大同}} 2 (807 CE), General {{ill|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|ja|坂上田村麻呂}} founded the shrine, enshrining Benzaiten at a site called Ōno. * In {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文}} 2 (1662 CE), the shrine was relocated to its current location.
== Festivals ==
The Grand Festival is held annually on July 1, with an Evening Festival the day before on June 30.
The Evening Festival includes various ceremonial and entertainment events.
== Access ==
; Railway : 15-minute walk from {{ill|Hirosaki Station|ja|弘前駅}} on the JR Line.
